defs.name: EscrowError
defs.value:
pub enum EscrowError {

    /// Invalid instruction
    #[error("Invalid Instruction")]
    InvalidInstruction,

    #[error("No rent excemption")]
    NotRentExempt,

    #[error("Amount mismatch")]
    ExpectedAmountMismatch,

    #[error("Authority is invalid")]
    InvalidAuthorityId,

    #[error("Amount overflow")]
    AmountOverflow,

    #[error("Account already settled")]
    AccountAlreadySettled,

    #[error("Fee overflow")]
    FeeOverflow,

    #[error("Account settled")]
    AccountNotSettled,
}

defs.name: InitEscrow
defs.docs: Starts the trade by creating and populating an escrow account and transferring ownership of the given temp token account to the PDA

attributes.value: / Starts the trade by creating and populating an escrow account and transferring ownership of the given temp token account to the PDA
/ 0. `[signer]` The account of the payer initializing the escrow
/ 1. `[signer]` The escrow authority responsible for approving / refunding payments due to some external conditions
/ 2. `[writable]`Temporary token account that should be created prior to this instruction and owned by the payer
/ 3. `[writable]` The escrow account, it will hold all necessary info about the trade.

defs.name: amount
defs.docs: The total amount of token X to be paid by the payer

attributes.value: / The total amount of token X to be paid by the payer
/ 1. `[writable]` The taker's token account for the token they will receive should the trade go through
/ 2. `[writable]` The fee taker's token account for the token they will receive should the trade go through
/ 3. `[writable]` The PDA's temp token account to get tokens from and eventually close
/ 4. `[writable]` The fee payer's main account to send their rent fees to
/ 5. `[writable]` The escrow account holding the escrow info

defs.name: fee
defs.docs: the amount the fee taker expects to be paid from amount

attributes.value: / the amount the fee taker expects to be paid from amount
/ 1. `[writable]` The escrow account holding the escrow info
/ 2. `[writable]` The fee payer's main account to send their rent fees to
